        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(wandb): native gRPC sandbox provider",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a native Go W&B Sandboxes provider (`provider: wandb`, alias `weights-and-biases`) backed by CoreWeave Sandboxes gRPC (`coreweave.sandbox.v1beta2`). No Python shim is used.\n\nWhy it matters: users who already ran `wandb login` can use the existing W&B API key from env/config/`~/.netrc`, so onboarding is just `--provider wandb --no-sync`.\n\n## Design\n\n- **Lifecycle:** acquire a short-lived sandbox, run an idle keepalive command, poll until `running`, execute one command, then stop unless `--keep` / `--keep-on-failure` applies.\n- **Auth precedence:** `CRABBOX_WANDB_API_KEY` → `wandb.apiKey` → `WANDB_API_KEY` → `~/.netrc`. The generic `WANDB_API_KEY` fallback is resolved in the W&B client so it cannot overwrite explicit config.\n- **Transport:** one cached TLS gRPC connection per backend instance; endpoint defaults to `api.cwsandbox.com:443` and can be overridden with `CWSANDBOX_BASE_URL`.\n- **Safety:** default max lifetime is 30 minutes; live smoke uses 60 seconds.\n- **Scope:** exec-only delegated-run provider. SSH, sync, desktop/browser, and warmup are intentionally unsupported.\n\n## Testing\n\n- CI green on the squashed head: Go, Docs, Plugin, Worker, Release Check, Socket checks.\n- Local full suite: `go test -race ./...`.\n- Acceptance tests: `go test ./internal/cli ./internal/providers/wandb ./internal/providers/all`.\n- Unit coverage includes provider contracts: keep-on-failure, env forwarding, `--id` + env rejection, timing JSON on failures, list-all behavior, warmup rejection, auth precedence, netrc parsing, status normalization, and gRPC error exit-code mapping.\n- Live e2e verified against the real gateway: `Version → Acquire → Exec → Stop`.\n\n```sh\nexport CRABBOX_WANDB_API_KEY=...\ngo test -tags smoke -run TestSmokeVersionAndExec -v ./internal/providers/wandb/\nCRABBOX_LIVE=1 scripts/wandb-smoke.sh\n```",
